description: From Middle French ïambique, from Late Latin iambicus, from Ancient Greek ἰαμβικός (iambikós), from ἴαμβος (íambos) + -ικός (-ikós).

adjectives.description: iambic (comparative more iambic, superlative most iambic)

entries.meaning: (prosody) Consisting of iambs (metrical feet with an unstressed-stressed pattern) or characterized by their predominance. [from 16th c.]
(prosody) An iamb; a line or group of lines of iambs.
